commit 320a7dad29c25a5e1c8fbfb39858f7573a25aa29
Author: Daniela Brozzoni <danielabrozzoni@protonmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 14 08:28:14 2026 +0000

    Retry connect failures and lower default IP concurrency
    
    A connect timeout/refusal isn't reliable evidence of a dead peer -- it
    can be self-inflicted by a saturated worker pool, so treat it like any
    other transient failure and retry up to handshake_attempts before
    giving up as Unreachable. Also drop the default ip-concurrency from
    512 to 64 to reduce that self-inflicted saturation.

